  "text": "The study endpoint was MACE, a term that comprises allcause death, any repeat PCI, recurrent MI, and coronary artery bypass graft. Nonfatal recurrent MI was defined as the development of recurrent angina symptoms accompanied by changes in 12-lead electrocardiogram or increased levels of cardiac-specific biomarkers. Repeat PCI included target lesion revascularization, target vessel revascularization, and non-target vessel revascularization [CITATION_1] .",
